---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { formatDate } from "@/lib/format";

const lastUpdated = formatDate("2026-04-16T00:00:00Z");
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of use" path="/terms" pageWidth="wide" pageClass="pt-10">
  <article class="rm-prose max-w-[56rem]">
    <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    <p>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    <p>rightmodel.dev is a free tool that recommends AI model tiers based on task descriptions.</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Informational only.</strong> Recommendations are generated from heuristic rules and
      publicly available model pricing. Actual model performance and cost may vary based on your
      prompt structure, usage patterns, and provider pricing changes not yet reflected in the current
      snapshot.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>No warranty.</strong> This tool is provided as is without warranty of any kind. No
      guarantee is made about the accuracy or suitability of any recommendation.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Limitation of liability.</strong> To the fullest extent permitted by law, the operator
      is not liable for damages arising from your use of this tool.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Acceptable use.</strong> You agree not to disrupt the service, scrape it in ways that
      degrade service for others, or misrepresent rightmodel output as official vendor guidance.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Third-party content.</strong> rightmodel references model names and pricing belonging to
      Anthropic, Google, and OpenAI. Those names and trademarks belong to their respective owners.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Source code.</strong> rightmodel is open source under the MIT licence. Repository:
      <a href="https://github.com/rightmodel/web">github.com/rightmodel/web</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Changes.</strong> These terms may be updated. The last updated date above reflects the
      current version.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Contact.</strong> Questions: <a href="https://github.com/rightmodel/web/issues">open an issue</a>
      or reach me via <a href="/about">About</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
